Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.56,0:11:37.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们的屏幕不放大的话 就看不清所有的细节\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if ourview screen were not enhanced to show us all the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.40,0:11:40.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,四散的暗珠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The dark globs scattered about...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:43.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,称为[PROPLYD] 即原行星盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called proplyds or protoplanetary disks...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:47.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是新生恒星周围的尘埃毯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are blankets of dust surrounding newly formed stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.49,0:11:52.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被四边形强大的星际风压缩成了水滴状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forced into teardrop shapes by energetic stellarwinds...from the Trapezium.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.46,0:11:54.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中之一清晰地表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of them clearly shows...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.83,0:11:58.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,环状碎片围绕着中央恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a ring of debris orbiting its central star...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.25,0:12:01.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有力地证明了新的行星系统正在形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}strong evidence that a new system of planets is forming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:07.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们离开猎户星云的路线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our route out of the Orion Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.30,0:12:10.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,向我们展示了从地球看它的角度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shows us the angle at which we see it from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.27,0:12:13.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 在1300光年以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But at 1,300 light-years away...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.94,0:12:17.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它退缩成了我们视野里的一个小不点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it shrinks to a minor smudge in our field ofview.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.28,0:12:23.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,想象一下在距离只有4光年的最近的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lmagine how it would look at only four light-years...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.20,0:12:26.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所见到的情景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the distance to the nearest star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:27.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,猎户星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Orion Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.28,0:12:29.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们距离猎户星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ifwe were as close to the Orion Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.83,0:12:33.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如其最近的恒星那样 那么它就会明亮到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the nearest star is to us, it would be so bright...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:37.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就不知道居然还会有夜空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we wouldn't be aware of the dark sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.04,0:12:38.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就不会看到其它星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We wouldn't see the other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.29,0:12:40.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们几乎不知道还有其它星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would almost not be aware of other galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.55,0:12:42.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是因为它太明亮了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just because it would be so bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.47,0:12:47.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,整个世界将只是猎户星云和太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The whole world would be the Orion Nebula and the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.97,0:12:52.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,幸运的是 我们偏居星系一隅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately, we live at a point in the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.85,0:12:56.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在这里我们的望远镜和相机可以梳理天穹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where our telescopes and cameras can comb the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.65,0:13:00.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,抖散这些珠宝-星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to shake loose the gems we call nebulas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.98,0:13:02.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,共有五个大类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are five major kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.61,0:13:08.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星形成星云 比如被称为的HⅡregions猎户星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Star-forming nebulas like Orion are called H-ll regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:10.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,H-Ⅱ表现了稀薄的氢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}H-ll describes the thin hydrogen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:13.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,受到恒星发出的光的激发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}excited by hot stars to emit light.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.12,0:13:18.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在其他地方存在着反射星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln other places, there are reflection nebulas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.67,0:13:22.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,亮星驱散周围的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the bright stars have driven away the surrounding gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:25.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,留下尘埃反射星光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving mostly dust to reflect starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.55,0:13:32.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星状星云形成于普通恒星的垂死阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planetary nebulas are formed...during the slow, dying stages of ordinary stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.18,0:13:37.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会在星系中产生一些最有趣的形状和颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and produce some of the most intriguing displays...of shape and color in the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.02,0:13:43.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星残骸也是恒星消亡的残留物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Supernova remnants are also leftovers from stellar deaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.53,0:13:48.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过是大质量恒星生命结束于巨大的爆炸之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but from massive stars, which end their lives in immense explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.53,0:13:53.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最后是暗星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And finally, there are the dark nebulas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.29,0:13:55.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星际气体和尘埃云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}clouds of interstellar gas and dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.83,0:13:58.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被看见通常是因为它们在背后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}visible usually because they appear in silhouette...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.87,0:14:01.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,明亮的星云衬托下才表现出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}against the bright nebulas behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.29,0:14:05.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,迟早会有恒星在其中突然诞生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln time, stars will burst into existence within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:12.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 星系里最原始的星云 气体尘埃云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the very origin of the galaxy's clouds of stars, gas, and dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:14.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,全都是最耐人寻味的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the most intriguing phenomenon of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.27,0:14:18.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来自神秘的星际介质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Springing from the mysterious interstellar medium...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.31,0:14:21.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星云之谜就在于它们怎么能够\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the riddle of the nebulas is how they can form...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.56,0:14:24.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成于一无所有之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from what is almost nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:29.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在太空虚无缥缈间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space, in its vast emptiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.70,0:14:32.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,远不止眼前这些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has much more to it than meets the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.37,0:14:41.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在太阳与邻居之间充满了中性星际介质[ISM]\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Filling the distances between the Sun and all its galactic neighbors...is the neutral interstellar medium or lSM.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.83,0:14:44.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们打量星际间漆黑一片时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we think about the blackness between stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.63,0:14:47.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时 会以为没有什么东西而是真空一片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we sometimes think there's nothing there but the vacuum of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.72,0:14:50.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 实际上 即使所谓的真空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But actually, even the so-called vacuum of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.55,0:14:52.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也是充满了尘埃和气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is full of dust and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:54.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在它相当的稀薄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, it's quite rarefied.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.18,0:14:55.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有多稀薄？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How rarefied?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.31,0:14:59.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许比我们在地球上创造的真空还要真空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps better than the best vacuum...we can create on the planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:04.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星际介质里的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The particles in the interstellar medium...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.73,0:15:08.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,九成是氢原子 一成是氦原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are ninety percent hydrogen atoms, ten percent helium...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.86,0:15:12.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,极微量的其他元素和细微的尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and trace amounts of other elements and tiny specks of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.83,0:15:17.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体和尘埃的存在是明显的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Existence of the gas and dust is evident...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:19.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过观察银河系里的恒星带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by looking at the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.12,0:15:24.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们从地球看到的侧面像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the band of stars we see in the edge-on view...of our home galaxy from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.84,0:15:29.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在那儿黑暗的空间里似乎空无一物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There, the dark spaces seem to be empty...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.09,0:15:32.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而事实上情况恰恰相反\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in reality, the opposite is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.64,0:15:36.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些空间里并不缺乏恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those spaces aren't devoid of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.60,0:15:40.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们实际上是尘埃 在我们与银河系的平面上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're actually dust between us and the distant stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.68,0:15:41.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,的遥远的恒星之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the plane of our galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.94,0:15:45.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,阻挡了光线 你看到的是它们的身影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they block that light, and you see them in silhouette.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.19,0:15:49.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体尘埃的黑色通道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The black lanes of gas and dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.44,0:15:51.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,表明星际介质以其最原始的形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}show us where the interstellar medium...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.36,0:15:55.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,纠结在一起形成了星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is clumping together to form nebulas in their most primeval form.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.99,0:16:02.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们看到在背景恒星里的星云剪影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see these dark nebulas as shadows against the background stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.58,0:16:06.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,蛇星云距离650光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Snake Nebula is 650 light-years distant...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:09.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,跨度3光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and approximately three light-years across.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.63,0:16:13.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,更暗的是巴纳德68\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even darker is Barnard 68...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.05,0:16:15.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以爱德华·埃莫森·巴纳德的名字命名\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}named for Edward Emerson Barnard...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.18,0:16:17.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他就是发现它的人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the astronomer who discovered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.26,0:16:21.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种星云似乎遮挡身后的星光够深邃的了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such nebulas may be deep enough..to block light from stars behind them...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.81,0:16:25.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 其中的气体尘埃 还是非常稀薄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the gas and dust inside them is still very thin...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.35,0:16:29.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直至引力的作用提速为止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is until gravity's work accelerates.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.19,0:16:30.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力就是吸引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity is attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.94,0:16:33.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从而大团的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a consequence, we have lumps of gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:36.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,无论其多么稀薄 一直被引力吸引着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no matter how rarefied, being attracted by gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.03,0:16:41.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直到产生凝聚的核质团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until we have clumps of nuclear material condensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:44.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着引力开始压缩气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As gravity begins to compress the gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.04,0:16:47.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,温度开始升高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it starts to heat up in temperature...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.04,0:16:49.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,产生恒星的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating the temperatures of a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.67,0:16:55.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,新的恒星横空出世\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The new stars burst into existence...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.51,0:16:59.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以其斑斓的光辉照亮了周遭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lighting up their surroundings with colorful brilliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.26,0:17:02.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,残留的暗星云形成了鲜明的对照\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Remaining dark nebulas stand out in stark contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.06,0:17:06.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和亮星云一样它们的形状决定了其名字\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like bright nebulas, their shapes suggest names.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.52,0:17:10.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,象鼻星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Elephant's Trunk Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:12.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,椎状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Cone Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.07,0:17:15.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,火焰星云 它的明暗区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Flame Nebula, where dark and light areas...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.11,0:17:18.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,创造了空中最引人入胜的景象之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}create one of the sky's most dramatic images.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.58,0:17:22.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,产星区的亮丽色彩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The brilliant colors of the star-forming regions...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.41,0:17:27.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,缘自星云气体受到附近炙热的新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}come from nebular gases excited by invisible ultraviolet radiation...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.21,0:17:30.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发出的紫外线激发而成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from nearby hot new stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.71,0:17:33.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些星发出的光 紫外光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light, the ultraviolet light from those stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.63,0:17:37.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,剥离了周围气体里的电子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is stripping offthe electrons in the gas in its immediate vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.22,0:17:42.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些电子游荡数天乃至数周\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These electrons float around for days orweeks...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.14,0:17:44.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最后找上裸露的质子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then ultimately find a bare proton...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:49.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或其它正电荷的核子 于是它们跳上轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or other positively charged nucleus, and they'll hop on to orbits...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:52.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此时 就会发出光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as they do, they'll emit light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.99,0:18:00.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,罗切斯特大学 天文学家 亚当·弗兰克\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the University of Rochester, astronomerAdam Frank...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.66,0:18:04.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将星云里的气体激荡比作篮球比赛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compares the excitement of gases in a nebula to a basketball game.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.00,0:18:11.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,篮球比赛真的是个好比喻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This basketball game is a real nice analogy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.29,0:18:13.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管俗气 但对星云还是很贴切的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}though earthbound, forwhat happens in a nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:23.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,场边 你观看罗切斯特大学对阵纽约大学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Down on the court, you got Rochester going up against NYU.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.64,0:18:27.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,篮球运动员很像星云中心的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The basketball players are a lot like the stars at the center of the nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.73,0:18:29.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,场上发生精彩时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When something exciting happens on the court...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:31.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你会看到大家群情激昂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll see the crowd getting all excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.82,0:18:39.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,雀跃欢呼 释放能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crowd stands up, they cheer, they emit energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.32,0:18:40.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在这里是声能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln this case it's sound energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.53,0:18:41.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而在星云里 就是光能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in the nebula, it would be light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.99,0:18:43.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,情况完全一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is exactly the same thing that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.83,0:18:45.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,电子被剥离原子后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when an electron gets ripped off an atom...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.66,0:18:47.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,游荡上一会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flies around for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:48.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后找上另一个原子与之合并\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then finds another atom to recombine with...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:50.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同时释放出能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and emits energy at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.34,0:19:01.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,新星在星云里诞生时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As new stars are born within the nebulas...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.01,0:19:05.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有时会发出壮观的喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they sometimes shoot out spectacularjets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.60,0:19:09.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个有3万亿英里长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This one is three trillion miles long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:11.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,喷射是星云凭着自身的条件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thejets are nebulas in their own right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.56,0:19:14.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过气体尘埃云的旋转产生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generated by the orbiting cloud of gas and dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.69,0:19:16.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将物质送给年轻的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sending material into the young star.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.99,0:19:21.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为旋转它首先形成一个吸积盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because of rotation, it first forms an accretion disk...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.61,0:19:23.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,犹如飞碟围绕着年轻恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is kind of like a Frisbee spinning around the young star...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.03,0:19:25.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,喂养 打造着年轻的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}feeding, building the young star.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.03,0:19:28.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在这个气体中始终存在着磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, there's always magnetic fields in all of this gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.58,0:19:30.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着圆盘的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as the disk spins...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.04,0:19:32.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物质沿着磁力线堆积 这么说吧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}material loads up on the field lines, as we say...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:35.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它盘旋而上然后被抛入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it spins and then it's flung out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.50,0:19:37.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最终磁力线旋转而出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, the field lines get bent around...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.71,0:19:40.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,校准喷射 创造出漂亮而坚实的射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}collimating thejet, creating a nice solid jet column.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.39,0:19:45.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,除了星际喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Along with stellarjets...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.26,0:19:48.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星云还会表现出狂野的变种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the galaxy's nebulas display a wild variety...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.52,0:19:54.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气泡 冲击波 气柱 甚至高山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of bubbles, shockwaves, pillars, and even mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.57,0:19:59.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些叫做创世群山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are called the Mountains of Creation...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.74,0:20:03.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个星云经常来对比著名的创造之柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a nebula often compared to the famous Pillars of Creation...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.62,0:20:07.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 事实上 要大上10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but, in fact, ten times as large.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:11.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管它们有70光年宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Though they are seventy light-years across...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:14.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这幅图片拍自可见光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this image, taken in visible light...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.33,0:20:16.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,展现了它们细微的外貌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shows them subtle in appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.88,0:20:20.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过来看看我们通过史匹哲太空望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But see what happens when we look at a picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.34,0:20:25.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,用红外线拍摄的照片的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Spitzer Space Telescope, which views them in infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.93,0:20:31.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,红外线是波长比可见光略长的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lnfrared light is light of a slightly longerwavelength than visible light.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.43,0:20:32.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比红光更加红\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's redder than red light.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.77,0:20:35.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们通常看到的发出红外线的物体 比如我们自己\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We commonly see infrared light from objects like us...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.94,0:20:38.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,温暖但不是极热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are warm, but not extremely hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.53,0:20:43.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于 红外线是温暖的物体发出的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since infrared light is emitted by anything that is warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.95,0:20:47.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 通常被用来检测热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's often used to detect heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.12,0:20:50.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过特殊的相机各种温度都可以检测到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln special cameras, each temperature is detected...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:53.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于红外线我们无法看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as an infrared color that we can't see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.37,0:20:57.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是它就被转换成可见光让我们能看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then it's translated into a visible color that we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.13,0:21:02.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是红外线可以利用体温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's how infrared can use body heat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.71,0:21:06.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来展现某些业余天文学家晚间工作的道理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to reveal some amateur astronomers working in the dark of night...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.80,0:21:10.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,否则我们将不得不打开灯光来看他们了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when otherwise we'd have to turn on a light to see them at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.98,0:21:15.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在太空中道理是一样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln space, the same principle applies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.85,0:21:19.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是可见光下的天鹰星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the Eagle Nebula as seen in visible light...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.82,0:21:23.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是史匹哲太空望远镜的红外观察就大为不同了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the infrared Spitzer Telescope sees it in a much different way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.99,0:21:29.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,揭示出一个极热的尘埃区 这里红色的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}revealing a region of extremely hot dust, seen here in red.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.49,0:21:32.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在你不得不思量究竟是什么使得尘埃这么热的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, you have to ask yourself, what could get dust that hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.16,0:21:34.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是星云里的恒星吗？不\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars in the nebula? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.12,0:21:36.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们还不够亮 不够热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're not really bright enough, they're not hot enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.16,0:21:37.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么 或许是超新星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but maybe a supernova explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:42.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许是恒星的猝死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe the violent death of a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.55,0:21:46.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星会发出巨大的冲击波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova would send out a massive shockwave...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.26,0:21:48.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能产生深远的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which might have a profound impact...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.47,0:21:52.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 天鹰星云是创造之柱的所在地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the Eagle Nebula is home to the Pillars of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.47,0:21:54.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于创造之柱来说看上去并不很好\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, for the Pillars, it doesn't look very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.98,0:22:00.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,接下来的情况是爆发恒星发出的超新星冲击波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's going to happen is that supernova shockwave...that's expanding out from the exploding star...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.73,0:22:04.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,迟早会击中创造之柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sooner or later is going to hit those Pillars.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.11,0:22:07.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦击中创造之柱就会将其蒸发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when it hits the Pillars, it's going to evaporate them...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.11,0:22:09.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们会消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're going to be destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.49,0:22:13.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,留下目前正在创造之柱背后形成的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving the stars that are currently forming in the Pillars behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.95,0:22:16.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而所有那些漂亮的气体尘埃 也就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but all that gas and dust in those beautiful, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.66,0:22:19.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,柱状的东西都将消失殆尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pillar-like shapes, they're going to go, just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.59,0:22:25.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,揭示著名的创造之柱命运的红外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The infrared that reveals the fate of the famous Pillars...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.17,0:22:29.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只不过是天文学家光线工具箱里的一件工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is only one tool in the astronomer's light box...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.05,0:22:32.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 星云可以通过各种光线来观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the nebulas can be seen in light of all kinds...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.35,0:22:37.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,拨开迷雾 揭示它们一直保持的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stripping away shrouds that keep their secrets otherwise hidden forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.65,0:22:43.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在充满光线的宇宙里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln a universe filled with light...
