Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.98,0:28:56.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,主导了行星状星云的全彩照片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dominate true color photos of planetary nebulas.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:28:59.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,环状星云是个典型的例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Ring Nebula is a prime example.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.90,0:29:07.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它距离地球2300光年 直径1.3光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is 2,300 light-years from Earth and 1.3 light-years in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.20,0:29:10.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被认为是行星状星云的原型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is considered a prototype for planetary nebulas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.33,0:29:14.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而环状星云的形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the shape of the Ring Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.04,0:29:16.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比其它行星状星云来得简单\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is simple compared to other planetary nebulas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.29,0:29:21.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,惊奇地发现这样的表现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's remarkable to realize that displays like these...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.63,0:29:26.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,伴随着宇宙间几乎每一颗恒星的消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}accompany the death of nearly every star in the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.97,0:29:31.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,包括50亿年后我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including our own Sun in about five billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.14,0:29:36.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星在生命行将结束时会膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The star swells up near the end of its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.52,0:29:38.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳会撑满半个天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun will fill half the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.44,0:29:40.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,日落西山时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the sun is setting in the west...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.98,0:29:43.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳的另一部分会在东方冉冉升起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another part of it will be rising in the east...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.65,0:29:45.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到了中午整个天空将会被这个通红的天体填满\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at noon, the whole sky will be filled...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.70,0:29:50.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把我们烧成陶器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with this bright red object, baking us to porcelain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.45,0:29:56.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此时恒星内部变得狂躁不安\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this point, the inside of the star becomes wildly unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.46,0:29:59.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它歇业了 颤抖了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it shutters, and it quakes...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.29,0:30:03.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那时其表面非常松散\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at that point, the surface, which is very loosely bound...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.71,0:30:05.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会被抛进太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can be tossed into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.51,0:30:09.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以将它看作星际喷嚏的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of it as a process of stellar sneezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.64,0:30:16.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,外层气体的膨胀伴随着太阳从红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outer envelope of gas expands as the Sun shrinks from a red giant...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.35,0:30:18.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,塌缩成炙热的白矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to become a hot white dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.52,0:30:21.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,矮星的紫外线激发周围的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The dwarf's ultraviolet light excites the surrounding gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.02,0:30:25.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,使其发光 犹如产星区里的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}causing it to glow just as in star-forming regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.74,0:30:30.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光芒四射会持续数千年才会消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The brilliant display will last for thousands ofyears before fading away.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.58,0:30:38.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳在其生命终结时将会表现出何种宇宙图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just what kind of cosmic picture the Sun will paint at the end of its life...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.16,0:30:40.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几乎难以预料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is nearly impossible to predict.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.38,0:30:43.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是各种行星状星云惊人景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But witness the astounding variety...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.63,0:30:46.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在星系中比比皆是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of planetary nebulas throughout the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.59,0:30:50.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是什么让个个都灿烂各异？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What makes each one dazzlingly different?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.30,0:30:53.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是什么驱使它们的形状高深莫测？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what engines drive their enigmatic shapes?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.89,0:31:00.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们银河系里估计有一万个行星状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are an estimated 10,000 planetary nebulas in our galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.69,0:31:07.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每个都呈现出恒星独特的死亡方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}each one displaying the death of a star in its own unique way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.40,0:31:13.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管每个行星状星云都产生于一个恒星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although each planetary nebula is generated by a single star system...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.66,0:31:17.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它们的个头相比之下还是巨大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}their size in comparison is immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.91,0:31:20.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星状星云是庞大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planetary nebulas are huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.42,0:31:23.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果太阳系放在我的手指间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If l had the solar system between my fingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.38,0:31:29.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么行星状星云的半径会大上1000到10000倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the planetary nebula would be 1,000 to 10,000 times larger in radius.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.05,0:31:33.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 由于它们距离地球遥远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And yet, because of their great distance from Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.14,0:31:38.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,多数行星状星云呈现给我们的犹如宇宙间的小斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most planetary nebulas appear to us as tiny specks in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.35,0:31:44.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星状星云NGC 2440距离我们4000光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The distance to the planetary nebula NGC 2440 is 4,000 light-years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.69,0:31:48.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管星云本身有整整一光年宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And although the nebula itself is one full light-year across...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.65,0:31:51.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是其个头 从地球上看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its size, when viewed from Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.07,0:31:54.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只有满月宽度的4%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is only four percent as wide as the full Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.70,0:31:58.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只有最强大的望远镜才能看清其细节\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only the most powerful telescopes can see it in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.62,0:32:06.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,外观大小如月球的星云是螺旋星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A nebula as large as the Moon in apparent size is the Helix Nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.88,0:32:10.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 还是需要定时曝光照相才能看清全貌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it still requires a photo time-exposure to be seen at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.67,0:32:17.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其震撼的形状启迪了一些人将其称为"上帝之眼"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lts stunning form has inspired some people to call it the "Eye of God."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.68,0:32:20.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在450光年外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At about 450 light-years away...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.85,0:32:24.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是离地球最近的行星状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is among the closest planetary nebulas to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.48,0:32:28.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,正因为这样它一直被认真的研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As such, it has been studied intensely.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.15,0:32:31.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这张相片来自哈勃太空望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This photo from the Hubble Space Telescope...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.28,0:32:35.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是制作得最详尽的天文图像之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is one of the most detailed astronomical images ever made.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.53,0:32:37.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在其所揭示的惊奇之中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Among the surprises it reveals...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.91,0:32:42.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是星云内部有些奇怪的轮辐状的节点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are strange spoke-like knots inside the nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.16,0:32:43.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们称其为彗星节点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They call them cometary knots...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.79,0:32:47.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许是认为它们来自这颗恒星周围的古老的彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thinking maybe they're originally from old comets around this star...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.13,0:32:52.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而事实上这其实是星光与气体的自然互动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when, in fact, it's really a natural interaction...of the starlight with the gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.51,0:32:55.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在星光射出时像是在轰击气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the starlight comes out, it sort of shocks the gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.39,0:32:57.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像是在火上泼冷水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}kind of like throwing cold water on a hot fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.85,0:33:03.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,造成气体缠绕破碎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it causes the gas to sort of curl and fragment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.85,0:33:11.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星状星云表现出的灿烂色彩是伪装\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The brilliant colors seen in photos of planetary nebulas are deceiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.73,0:33:13.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果飞船靠近螺旋星云中央的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf a spaceship were near the central star...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.03,0:33:16.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,举个例子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the Helix Nebula, for instance...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.28,0:33:21.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发光的气体是根本看不见的 因为太稀薄了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the glowing gas would be practically invisible because it's so thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.79,0:33:26.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只有加速从行星状星云外围经过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only by speeding to the planetary nebula's outer reaches...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.12,0:33:27.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,景色才会有所变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would the view start to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.71,0:33:33.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们必须穿越约1000个太阳系的半径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would have to travel for about a thousand solar system radii...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.55,0:33:38.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,才能看到行星状星云里的发光气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before we began to see the glow of the gases...in the planetary nebula itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.51,0:33:42.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些看上去很像我们在地球上看到的极光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these would look a lot like the Aurora...that we see here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.43,0:33:44.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,色彩美不胜收\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The colors would be beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.77,0:33:48.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此后不久我们将结束星云的穿行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then shortly after that, we would finish flying through the nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.60,0:33:50.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,出没于太空深处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we would be out in the depths of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.90,0:33:55.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,回看星云 色彩更为清晰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Looking back on the nebula, the colors are more apparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.49,0:33:58.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,气体是在太稀薄了难以看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gas is otherwise too thin to be seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.20,0:34:01.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,除非 我们能够看透数十亿英里后的外壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unless we're looking through its entire envelope...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.24,0:34:04.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就如我们现在这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of miles thick, as we are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.12,0:34:07.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使 到了此时 我们还是需要得到帮助\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even at this point, we need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.54,0:34:12.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的眼睛预计看到的是氢元素的红色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our eyes see the expected hydrogen red...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.55,0:34:15.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 有更多的颜色显现出来 结构变得更加清晰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but more colors show up, and the structure becomes clearer...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.59,0:34:18.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只要我们的飞船用上哈勃调色板\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if our spacecraft applies the Hubble palette to ourview.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.64,0:34:24.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过我们看到的星云受限于我们的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Still, ourview of the nebula is limited by our position.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.85,0:34:26.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像从地球上观察一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as we do from Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.27,0:34:29.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们只能从一个方向进行观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're seeing it from only one direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.10,0:34:31.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它看上去就像是拉长的圆环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt looks like an elongated ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.61,0:34:34.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而我们的飞船快速围绕星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But our spacecraft speeds around the nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.44,0:34:38.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从另一个角度看会有很大的不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we realize that from another angle, it looks very different.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.95,0:34:41.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不是一个气体环 甚至球状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is not a ring of gas, or even a sphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.03,0:34:44.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是两个分开交叉的盘子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but two distinct intersecting disks...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.87,0:34:48.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可能缘自中央恒星在其生命周期行将终结时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}possibly caused by the central star discharging gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.25,0:34:50.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在两个不同的阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in two separate phases at different times...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.92,0:34:53.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以不同的时间将气体排放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}near the end of its life cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.46,0:34:59.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,围绕着行星状星云形状的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The questions surrounding the shapes of planetary nebulas...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.76,0:35:02.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是整个天文学中最令人困扰的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are among the most perplexing in all of astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.64,0:35:07.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来看一下行星状星云的其它形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's take a look at some of the shapes of planetary nebulae.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.64,0:35:11.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其形状从球形如柠檬片星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They range from round like the Lemon Slice Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.02,0:35:16.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到椭圆形如螺线图星云等好多好多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to elliptical like the Spirograph Nebula and many others...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.73,0:35:19.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以至到极端的例子如蚂蚁星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to extreme cases like the Ant Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.78,0:35:23.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,双鱿鱼星云 又称M2-9\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Double Squid Nebula, otherwise known as M2-9.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.49,0:35:28.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,由于恒星脱胎于球状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since a star starts out as a sphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.75,0:35:31.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可能预计其临终的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you might expect its dying gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.58,0:35:35.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会形成球状的行星状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to produce a spherical planetary nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.59,0:35:39.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但 实际上 只有10%的行星状星云具有这种形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, in fact, only ten percent of planetary nebulas have this shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.43,0:35:44.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有的动力中 隐藏在外来因素背后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Among the engines behind more exotic forms...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.30,0:35:46.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是来自层层气体的星际风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are the stellarwinds from different layers of gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.01,0:35:51.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是恒星在死亡过程的不同时段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thrown out by the star at different times in its death cycle...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.14,0:35:52.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以不同速度抛出的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at different speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.77,0:35:56.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你看到的是一套组合风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what you get is an interacting set ofwinds...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.52,0:35:58.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,内部的风之间相互撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}winds colliding with otherwinds from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.53,0:36:01.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是塑造星云的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a process that sculpts the nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.03,0:36:04.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,帮助形成了其有趣的形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and helps to give it its interesting shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.91,0:36:09.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最具魅力的行星状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most intriguing of the planetary nebulas...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.25,0:36:10.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是那些双极状的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are those with bipolar shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.21,0:36:14.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些怪物中的神秘力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mysterious forces within these strange objects...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.96,0:36:18.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把发光的气体射出喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cause glowing gas to shoot out injets...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.05,0:36:22.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,使人联想起恒星在诞生过程中的星际喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reminiscent of the stellarjets from stars in the process of being born.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.47,0:36:25.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这两个极其类似的现象怎么会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How could two so similar phenomena...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.01,0:36:30.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同时发生在恒星的诞生和死亡的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}happen at both the beginning and the end of stellar life?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.18,0:36:32.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,喷射是无处不有的天文现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jets are a ubiquitous phenomena in astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.56,0:36:34.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有这些喷射的共同点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What all thesejets have in common...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.94,0:36:36.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是都存在着积吸盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the presence of an accretion disk...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.94,0:36:38.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是一团旋转的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is rotating gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.77,0:36:41.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,旋转气体中存在磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}magnetic fields in the rotating gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.40,0:36:43.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当物质流过积吸盘时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as material flows through the accretion disk...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.57,0:36:44.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被拉进磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and loads on the field lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.91,0:36:46.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就被吹入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it gets blown back out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.91,0:36:52.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是垂死的恒星没有一个物质会掉进去的圆盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a dying star doesn't have a disk of material falling into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.25,0:36:55.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是除非是成双成对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is, unless it's a part of a binary pair...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.71,0:36:58.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两颗恒星互相围绕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}two stars orbiting around each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.50,0:37:02.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,双星在宇宙间是很普遍的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Binary pairs are very common in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.55,0:37:05.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两颗恒星相互围绕时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the two stars rotate around each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.26,0:37:08.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中一颗会将物质送给另一颗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of the stars is giving up mass to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.76,0:37:10.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物质从一颗流向另一颗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Material flows from one star to the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.60,0:37:12.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就形成了一个积吸盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you form an accretion disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.35,0:37:15.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,磁场就出现在那个积吸盘里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Magnetic fields appear in that accretion disk...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.44,0:37:18.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物质被吹走就如其它案例那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and material is blown off it just like in the other cases as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.32,0:37:25.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星状星云表现了整个空间的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planetary nebulas represent the normal processes...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.11,0:37:27.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星死亡的正常过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of star death throughout space.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.24,0:37:32.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 宇宙间存在着极不正常的巨人恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are giant stars in the universe...that are farfrom normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.50,0:37:35.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们在巨大的爆炸中结束自己的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They conclude their lives in massive explosions...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.41,0:37:39.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通常星云留下的是它们遭遇的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, often, the nebulas left behind are the only clues...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.29,0:37:42.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,惨烈终结的唯一的线索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tojust how they met theirviolent ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.72,0:37:50.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1054年一颗巨大的恒星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the year1054, a massive star blew up...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.35,0:37:54.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,距离太阳系有6300光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}6,300 light-years away from the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.48,0:38:01.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从地球上看似空中最亮的一颗新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the Earth, it appeared as a new star...the most brilliant in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.11,0:38:03.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比金星亮10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten times brighter than Venus...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.28,0:38:06.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大白天能看到有29天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was visible in broad daylight for 29 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.82,0:38:10.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它被中国的天文学家注意到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt was noted by Chinese astronomers...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.62,0:38:13.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许还有新墨西哥的阿纳萨齐人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps the Anasazi of New Mexico...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.33,0:38:15.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在他们的岩画中也看到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as seen in one of their petroglyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.16,0:38:20.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它的消失与出现一样突然\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt faded away almost as quickly as it appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.17,0:38:24.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如今 我们只能通过望远镜看到它了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and today we can see it only through telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.26,0:38:27.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而它留下的东西蔚为壮观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what's left of it is spectacular.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.34,0:38:31.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1000年后我们将它称为蟹状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A thousand years later, we call it the Crab Nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.35,0:38:36.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其是一种星云叫做超新星残骸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of a variety of nebulas known as supernova remnants.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.35,0:38:42.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星残骸其实是扩展的残片云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Supernova remnants are essentially the expanding debris clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.36,0:38:46.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来自巨大恒星的星际爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the stellar explosion of a really massive star.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.03,0:38:51.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是大质量恒星在其生命终结时的终极爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's the death explosion of that massive star at the end of its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.99,0:38:56.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星残骸类似于行星状星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Supernova remnants are something like planetary nebulas...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.58,0:39:00.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都来自恒星的终结\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in that each results from the death of a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.37,0:39:04.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在恒星首次演变成行星状星云时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a starfirst evolves to become a planetary nebula...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.71,0:39:08.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从其表面极其缓慢地喷出的稠密的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it ejects dense mass from its surface very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.88,0:39:11.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这不是爆发 只是喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is not an explosion, it's just an ejection.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.01,0:39:16.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星简单多了 就是爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova is much simpler. lt's just an explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.77,0:39:19.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一切就发生在几秒钟里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everything happens in seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.56,0:39:23.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们所看到的它周围的星云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the nebula that we see around it...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.23,0:39:25.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是残留的碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the shrapnel that still remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.32,0:39:34.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,爆发的冲击波轰击周围的物质使其发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light show comes from the explosion's shockwave...smashing into the surrounding material and causing it to glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.66,0:39:41.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其原理得到戏剧性的例证发生在2004年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The principle was dramatically illustrated...as it actually happened in 2004...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.96,0:39:45.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当时哈勃太空望远镜捕捉到了这个冲击波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the Hubble Space Telescope caught this shockwave...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.29,0:39:48.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在轰击超新星残骸里的气环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}striking a ring of gas in the remnant of a supernova...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.67,0:39:53.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它爆发于1987年16万光年外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that exploded 160,000 light-years away in 1987.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.26,0:40:01.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,言归正传蟹状星云仍然是最有名的超新星残骸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Closer to home, the Crab Nebula remains the most famous...of all supernova remnants.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.44,0:40:04.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过望远镜研究了300年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Studied through telescopes for 300 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.69,0:40:10.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中隐藏着一个秘密直到1968年才揭秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it contains a secret buried inside, undiscovered until 1968.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.95,0:40:16.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其最中心是一颗脉冲星 每秒钟旋转30次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the very center is a pulsar, spinning at thirty times per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.45,0:40:20.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,脉冲星是旋转的中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A pulsar is a spinning neutron star...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.12,0:40:24.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其密度大到一茶勺重达10亿吨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so dense that one teaspoon of it would weigh a billion tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.79,0:40:29.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,蟹状星云中的那个只有18英里的直径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The one inside the Crab Nebula is just eighteen miles across...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.59,0:40:31.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,却比太阳还重\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and weighs more than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.72,0:40:36.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它快速旋转 但因速度放缓而在丢失能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's spinning fast, but losing energy by gradually slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.01,0:40:40.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其转动能正在转移到气体里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the energy of its rotation is being transferred into the gas...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.43,0:40:44.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 星云里的大量辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, in fact, much of the radiation in that nebula...
